<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-27T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-27T23:00:00-05:00" n="491" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10637: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-28T12:00:00+08:00">November 28,
                                1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received November 28—3:20
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>1050. Department’s 388, November 26, 7 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>I am replying to the Minister for Foreign Affairs as indicated in
                                the Legation’s 1030, November 22, 10 p.m., third paragraph, but am
                                incorporating in the note the phraseology employed in paragraph 1 of
                                the Department’s telegram under reference.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>I am also telegraphing the text of the note to the commander in
                                chief and to the American Consul General at Canton and am informing
                                the latter of the content of paragraph 2 of the Department’s
                                telegram.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>